            <div corresp="#c4825f2">
                <head>Damascus, Syria</head>
                <p>George W. Young, Consul Cl. 8, detaited as Conaal in charge June 13, 1919;
                    appointed Consul Class 6 Sept. 5, 1919; detailed to Stoke-on-Trent July 14,
                    1921.</p>
                <p>Charles E. Allenflately at Constantinople) Consul Cl 6, was detailed to Damascus
                    as Consul in charge Apr. 26, 1921; detailed to Constantinople Feb. 24, 1923
                    effective upon expiration of leave of absence in U.S.; turned office over to
                    V.C. Keeley Mar. 31, 1923.</p>
            </div>
